str2: For. A primary particle; properly, assigning a reason.
In, on, among. A primary preposition denoting position, and instrumentality, i.e. A relation of rest; 'in, ' at, on, by, etc.
Each (of more than two), every one. As if a superlative of hekas; each or every.

parse: Verb - Present Indicative Active - 3rd Person Singular
str2: From pro and lambano; to take in advance, i.e. eat before others have an opportunity; to anticipate, surprise.
The, the definite article. Including the feminine he, and the neuter to in all their inflections; the definite article; the.
Pertaining to self, i.e. One's own; by implication, private or separate.
A dinner, an afternoon or evening meal. From the same as dapane; dinner, i.e. The chief meal.
A primary particle; properly, indicative of affirmation or concession; usually followed by a contrasted clause with de.

str2: To be hungry, needy, desire earnestly. From the same as penes; to famish; figuratively, to crave.

str2: To be intoxicated with wine, be drunk. From another form of methe; to drink to intoxication, i.e. Get drunk.
